metadata.name: pantonX.2 #60
metadata.description:
pantonX.2

I am a visual artist and have worked in the field of coding since the early years of processing.
Always loved geometric and minimalist art, bauhaus, De Stijl, Piet Mondrian, Ellsworth Kelly, Imi Knoebel -- just to name a few -- and last but not least Verner Panton, have had a big influence on my artistic work.

pantonX.2 is my second fxhash release. it's coded in p5js.
I set up a wider random range for the color arrays and the division structure, so that a 200x drop would have enough variation for not getting boring. 

"s" key is for saving

metadata.name: Kinetograms #306
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.description:
If you are thinking about having land and a house in the Morixels Land
You should buy Cows for your cats so that they don't get Hungry

The Morixels Toy are unique Random Generated 100 PFP NFTs.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 25 by 25 pixels and then resized to 1080 by 1080 resolution.
The number of Traits in this collection is 7 (148 layers) and it has the ability to make 206,388,000 NFTs.

Some ‚Äãlayers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.
To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

Twitter: @Morixels

Website: https://morixels.com/

metadata.name: ylb-mess-A #83
metadata.description:
With colors and shapes reminiscent of childhood LEGO explorations, 'ylb-mess-A' explores the assembly process in reverse, using recursive subdivision to create detailed structures instead of progressively building a complex structure brick by brick. Although the tools I use to explore and create have changed over the years, this piece reminds me of the natural creative curiosity that was instilled in me at an early age, for which I am incredibly grateful.

metadata.name: Vorticity #6
metadata.description:
Vorticity is a gpu-accelerated flow field. The particles in the flow field orbit around a set of points that move around over time.

Controls: Click and drag to push particles away. Press the space bar to pause the simulation, and again to resume. While paused, you can press "n" to advance the simulation a single step. Press "r" to restart the simulation (if you change the resolution of the screen after the page loads, you will need to restart to update the resolution).
